# Admin rules

Admin is a first-class product area, not a simple CRUD afterthought.

## Must include
- Role/permission-aware admin shell.
- User management with avatar/profile context.
- Content CMS for dictionary, kanji, grammar, examples, decks, BJT questions.
- Media library and provenance/license review.
- i18n management center.
- Import/export and audit logs.
- Admin analytics with real aggregate data paths.

## RBAC
Admin UI must hide or disable actions the user cannot perform. Backend must enforce permissions independently.

## Audit
Every admin write should create an audit event containing actor, action, target, timestamp, and before/after where appropriate.
